  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Sternal Wound Infection (SWI) in open heart surgery is one of the most annoying and avoidable&#xD;
      complications that one encounters during work. Investigators investigate the rates of sternal&#xD;
      wound infection (SWI) in patients in whom were used locking compression plates (LCP) versus&#xD;
      in patients in whom were used wires to fixate the sternum for variable causes. SWI increases&#xD;
      the overall cost and burden in the medical service and increases the patients suffering and&#xD;
      disability. investigators aim to provide our patients with the most suitable means for&#xD;
      sternal fixation.&#xD;
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
